  "text": "A possible element responsible for the high GST expression in CAPD patients might be the bioincompatibility of the PDF used, which can impair RBC metabolism either directly or via a challenge of the peritoneal tissue [CITATION_1] . However, in this study, we demonstrated that bicarbonate-based PDF, even if considered the most biocompatible PDF, induced the same GST overexpression in vivo as lactate-based PDF, thus suggesting that other factors can affect expression of the enzyme.",
